# Portfolio Conventions

Kim's World is a Next.js 15 / React 19 portfolio for Kim, a Principal Product Designer. Warm campfire palette, campfire visual concept, Good UX / Bad UX toggle.

## File & Naming Conventions

- **Components:** PascalCase filenames, one component per file (`Button.tsx`, `NavCard.tsx`)
- **Routes and content:** kebab-case (`thinking-about/`, `tinkered-and-delivered/`)
- **CSS variables:** `--{group}-{name}` — e.g. `--color-jade`, `--semantic-primary`, `--font-size-base`
- **Illustration slots:** kebab-case descriptive names — e.g. `hero-campfire`, `poll-pineapple`

## React Server Components

- **RSC by default.** Only add `"use client"` when the component needs hooks, interactivity, or browser APIs.
- Keep data fetching server-side where possible.

## Token-First Styling

- Use CSS custom properties from the token system: `bg-[var(--color-cream)]`, `text-[var(--semantic-text)]`
- **No naked/hardcoded values** — no raw hex, px, or rem values that aren't from tokens
- Token source of truth: `tokens/tokens.json` → `npm run build:tokens` → `app/globals.css`
- **NEVER edit `app/globals.css` directly**

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML (headings, landmarks, lists)
- ARIA labels on all interactive elements
- Keyboard navigation for all interactive elements
- Visible, styled focus indicators
- WCAG AA colour contrast

## Folder Responsibilities

```
app/                  # Pages only — no business logic
components/ui/        # Primitives (Button, Card, NavCard…)
components/features/  # Feature components (PollGame, UXToggle…)
lib/hooks/            # useAudio, useUXMode, useScrollReveal
lib/utils/            # Pure helpers
```
